        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 1:28PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 128 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles southwest of Hammon to 2 miles southeast
of Sayre. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Sayre...                          Berlin...
Stafford...                       Foss...
Canute...                         Foss Reservoir...
Elk City...                       Carter...
Butler...                         Hammon...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
